node.text:
This Asian Pacific Islander Heritage Month, our API community is sharing how their heritage inspires their creativity. Hear @the.korean.vegan’s powerful reflections on her grandmother and share your work with the hashtag #OurDearElders for a chance to be featured.

"I’ve partnered with @adobe to honor #OurDearElders, and today, I honor my grandmother. My brave, ferocious, loving grandmother. Who slipped out of North Korea through swamp water and cut through the mountains on foot, all while keeping my father safe. Tell me, how do you honor your elders? How have their stories shaped you? What are some of the foods you like to eat in remembrance of those who came before you? Share how you honor them with #OurDearElders so that we can all join in on this beautiful discussion." - Joanne Molinaro

node.text: What's the stitch? 🧵 Danielle Clough shares what inspires her to sew everything from pop culture icons to animals onto out-of-the-ordinary objects in this week's #WomenCreateWednesday.

node.accessibility_caption: A photo of Danielle's embroidery work on eight rackets, arranged as a bouquet. The colorful embroidery on each includes multiple types flowers, a snail, and a skull.

Photo of this week's feature, Danielle Clough. Her photo is in an arched frame with a white and orange background behind her. She is looking at the camera and smiling. Her blonde hair is in side buns with side-swept bangs, and she wears hoop earrings and a colorful apron over a black tee shirt. The text on the image says "Featuring Danielle Clough" in a vibrant pink color, and a circular red "Women Create Wednesday" logo is in the top right corner.
